# FlashBite - identity service HTTP examples (AT/RT hardening)
# Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension and JetBrains HTTP Client.
#
# Prereqs:
#   pnpm dev:identity      # http://localhost:3003
#   pnpm seed:users        # seed demo users (role@tenant.test)

@identityUrl = http://localhost:3003

### Identity health. Expect 200 { "status": "ok" }.
GET {{identityUrl}}/health

### Log in as a berlin merchant. Expect 201 { accessToken, tokenType: "Bearer", expiresIn: 900 }.
# @name login
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "merchant@berlin.test",
  "password": "devpassword"
}

### Refresh the access token (sends the fb_rt cookie set by login)
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/refresh

### Logout (revokes the refresh token)
POST {{identityUrl}}/auth/logout

### JWKS - public keys used to verify access tokens. Expect 200 { "keys": [ ... ] }
# Current + previous kid are both published so in-flight ATs survive a key rotation.
GET {{identityUrl}}/.well-known/jwks.json
